Prerequisite of the project:
# Need to install the python3 
# GO to the project path directory
# run the below command to activiate the flask env
$ source bin/activate
now you should see (flask) on the left of the command line. Let's install flask
# Install flask to run the REST API
# Need to install the python packages dependencies 
# Run the project via below command
$ python3 run-app.py



$ virtualenv flask
then

$ cd flask
let's activate the virtualenv

$ source bin/activate
now you should see (flask) on the left of the command line. Let's install flask

$ pip install flask
Then create a file hello.py
$ vi hello.py
------------------------------------
from flask import Flask
app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def hello():
    return "Hello World!"

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run()
------------------------------------

and run it with

$ python hello.py
